Today, we are excited to announce that MACRO has closed a new strategic funding round with an incredible group of blue-chip investors. @BlackRock Alternatives, @HarbourviewEP, and @GoldmanSachs - sincerest gratitude for believing in us and joining us on this important journey of taking MACRO to the next level.

We wouldn’t be where we are without the unwavering support of our existing and esteemed investors. My deepest thanks to all of you.  
This new infusion of capital will supercharge growth across MACRO’s business verticals and partnerships, including (our) representation firm M88. This positions us to unleash the full potential of the MACRO ecosystem and to continue building upon the vast media and entertainment opportunities that exist globally.  
I’m immensely grateful to all of our MACRO family, partners and collaborators who have helped us to push the needle forward, and bring our mission to life. This is the fulfillment of a dream and we are not done yet. #stayMACRO

We are pleased to announce that we have partnered with General Motors to launch The General Motors Marketing Academy Powered by MACRO, a five-month program to prepare the next generation of multicultural marketing executives. This program focuses on business and professional acumen, enabling each participant to successfully grow in marketing and media while creating a diverse talent pipeline of skilled and deserving executives in marketing, branding, public relations, and communications.  

The General Motors Marketing Academy, powered by MACRO, will identify eight exceptionally diverse candidates in the early stages of their careers for this curriculum-centered opportunity. During monthly meetings, best-in-class marketing executives, storytellers, speakers, and advisors will discuss topics such as scalability, best practices, market trends, positioning, navigating the corporate structure, and building a client base. Participants will also partake in on-site experiential sessions and will be paired with a marketing or media executive mentor to aid in their professional development. 

“It is a thrill and an honor to work with GM in creating this unique initiative to identify and support executives and entrepreneurs in the brand storytelling space,” said Stacey Walker King, Chief Brand Officer, MACRO.

Applications for The General Motors Marketing Academy are now open and will close on April 15, 2023. 

To learn more and to apply, please visit GMmarketingacademy.com

We’re excited to announce another first for MACRO! We have partnered with @iheartpodcast and will release #ShatteringTheSystem, a podcast that investigates a variety of crimes and exposes the systems and structures that make it possible for criminals of all kinds to get away with the unthinkable.

Hosted by celebrated audio journalist Sonari Glinton (@sonari1) and executive produced by Jonathan Unger (@ungermedia) and Roy Orecchio (@leftclick), the 10 episode series will debut on August 3rd and will air every Thursday.

Shout out to our colleague Aisha Wynn (@aishacorpaswynn) and team for leading the charge on our behalf.  #stayMACRO

We couldn’t be more excited to welcome Jamila Hunter @jamilasheree to our family as President of MACRO Television Studios! 

She most recently served as Executive Vice President of Original Programming and Development at Freeform and previously was President of Kenya Barris’ production company Khalabo Ink Society, after making her mark at ABC Entertainment, OWN, 20th Century Fox Television and Bravo, just to name a few.

Undeniably one of the most stellar and accomplished executives in TV, we look forward to adding Jamila’s wealth of knowledge, leadership skills and extensive experience to MACRO to help propel us to the next level.

#stayMACRO

📸: @kwakualston

I couldn’t be more proud as MACRO continues to build our leadership team. Today, we would all like to welcome Reena Singh @reenaksingh331 as our Executive Vice President, Head of Scripted Television! 

Hailing from her latest role as Disney Branded Television’s Senior Vice President of Live Action Series where she oversaw all extensions of programming, Reena brings her multi-genre experience to MACRO Television Studios after sharpening her skills at 20th Television Studios, USA Network, and ABC Network News. 

As one of Cynopsis’ Top Women In Media in 2022, we can’t wait to see how Reena continues to innovate and disrupt the entertainment industry 
as she joins our team.

Happy Friday, everyone! Flashing back to earlier this week when we kicked off awards season. I was honored to accept the Producers Award at the @CriticsChoice Celebration of Cinema & Television, Black, Latino, and AAPI Achievements. It’s a blessing to represent the work of our entire MACRO family as well as the dream team producer village (Stephen Love, Mark Wright, Datari Turner, Jamie Foxx, Juel Taylor, Tony Rettenmaier, James Lopez, Poppy Hanks, Jack Murray and Kim Roth) behind THEY CLONED TYRONE.

In addition to having my family by my side with so many friends and colleagues in the room, receiving the award from #TheyClonedTyrone’s @johnboyega was the perfect icing on the cake. 

Thank you again for the incredible recognition! 

#fbf #CriticsChoice #CCCelebration #Netflix #stayMACRO

Finishing up the year with a great addition to the MACRO Film Studios team! Please welcome Christine Otal @christineotal as she joins us as Senior Vice President of Production & Development. 

From her recent stint as Senior Vice President of Film at Bad Robot Productions, where she worked on numerous successful projects for Paramount, Warner Bros, and Amblin, to her role as Vice President of Development and Production at Millennium Films, where the film projects she produced grossed over $630 million at the box office, we couldn’t be more excited to have Christine in our MACRO family!

#stayMACRO

It’s challenging to find the words to truly capture my deep gratitude for receiving the Milestone Award from the PGA. It was just under 9 years ago that I took the biggest leap of faith to launch MACRO. 

Over the years, I’ve had amazing, mission-aligned colleagues, partners and investors and we’ve collaborated with the most talented producers, filmmakers, artists and studio partners. Together, we have become a force that has disrupted our entire industry! 
 
I extend my sincerest thanks to Susan Sprung, Stephanie Allain, Donald DeLine, Michelle Byrd, and the entire PGA organization for continuing to be exemplary advocates for producers!
 
To be acknowledged for this accomplishment and stand among the luminaries of our industry is both incredibly humbling and a profound honor.

#PGA #pgaawards #stayMACRO

Heading back to the @Sundanceorg Film Festival for our 7th Annual MACRO Lodge and couldn’t be more excited about it!

With our open house and social hours to information sessions and conversations with the artists and filmmakers behind films like Freaky Tales, Luther: Never Too Much, The American Society of Magical Negroes, and more, our weekend schedule is filled with events for the community and the culture. 

I appreciate all the MACRO love, whether you’re online or on the mountain, and I look forward to rejoining our #Sundance family in Park City on January 19-21, 2024.

Go to www.StayMACRO.com for the complete listing of our MACRO Lodge programming at the #SundanceFilmFestival next weekend.

#stayMACRO
